data.title: Ashton Kutcher and Mila Kunis Have a Cute 'Love Story' Moment at Taylor Swift’s Eras Tour with Their 2 Kids
data.meta_description: In one fan-recorded video, Kunis appears to lower herself as if to “propose” to Kutcher, whom she married in 2015
data.text:
In one fan-recorded video, Kunis appears to lower herself as if to “propose” to Kutcher, whom she married in 2015

Mila Kunis and Ashton Kutcher’s family partied at Taylor Swift’s Eras Tour!

The longtime couple and their children — Wyatt Isabelle, 9, and Dimitri Portwood, 7 — seemed to thoroughly enjoy Swift's second Eras Tour show in London on Saturday, June 22.

In one fan-recorded video — with a caption saying Kunis “proposes” to Kutcher — the actress, 40, sang and danced to “Love Story” with her husband, 46. When Swift sang, “He knelt to the ground and pulled out a ring,” Kunis appeared to lower herself as if to propose to Kutcher.

The That ‘70s Show alums have been married since 2015.

Their daughter, who was leaning against the VIP section’s railing with friendship bracelets on her arms, was unaware of the cute moment happening behind her — as the Bad Moms actress, wearing a blue flannel button-up shirt, executed the “proposal” with the Two and a Half Men star.

Related: Taylor Swift Fan Catches Boyfriend's Proposal on Her Own Livestream at Eras Tour in Portugal (Exclusive)

Another video showed Dimitri and his dad entering a barricaded section and then busting a move to Swift’s “Blank Space.” Kutcher, wearing a white T-shirt and gray pants, paused several times to dance with his son, who wore a graphic white T-shirt and black pants. At one point, Kutcher picked up his son, and they embraced during the “Blank Space” chorus.

In 2023, Kutcher discussed parenting with PEOPLE, saying, "For me, the No. 1 role I will ever play is father … It's the most important role in my life."

Kunis and Kutcher weren’t the only celebrities at the Eras Tour stop. The two shared the VIP tent at Wembley Stadium with Tom Cruise, Greta Gerwig, Hugh Grant and Travis Kelce, among others.

Related: Taylor Swift Brings Out Paramore’s Hayley Williams for Surprise Duet at 2nd Eras Tour Show in London

Grant later took to social media to share his experience, writing, "Dear @taylorswift13. You have an incredible show, an amazing and v hospitable team and excellent if gigantic boyfriend." He also included a hashtag suggesting that they took tequila shots.

At the Friday show, Prince William, Prince George and Princess Charlotte attended and posed with Swift for a photo. The royal trio took another selfie with the 14-time Grammy winner and her NFL boyfriend.
